, for example, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">in DFID (2000), </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">‘Disability, poverty </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">and development’</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:6pt; vertical-align:super">16</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">DFID (2010), </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">‘Guidance note: Education for children with disabilities –</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> improving access and quality”</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">, </span><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/67664/edu-chi-disabil-guid-note.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">https://w</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">ww.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/67664/edu-chi-disabil-guid-note.pdf</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn15"></a><a href="#_ftnref15">[15]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:6pt; vertical-align:super">17</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">This survey was not published. Instead, its results, along with accompanying recommendations, were sent directly to former DFID Parliamentary </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">Under-Secretary of State Stephen O’Brien MP in September 2012, and were subsequently re-sent to DFID’s Education Policy Team in October 2012. A copy can be provided to the committee on request.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn16"></a><a href="#_ftnref16">[16]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:6pt; vertical-align:super">18</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">GCE UK (2012), ‘Equity and Inclusion for All in Education’ </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">- </span><a href="http://www.sightsavers.org/our_work/how_we_help/education/global_campaign_for_education/19148_J0468_GCE%20Community%20Summary%20Report.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.sightsavers.org/our_work/how_we_help/education/global_campaign_for_education/19148_J0468_GC</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">E%20Community%20Summary%20Report.pdf</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn17"></a><a href="#_ftnref17">[17]</a><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn18"></a><a href="#_ftnref18">[18]</a><span style="font-family:'Palatino Linotype'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn19"></a><a href="#_ftnref19">[19]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt">DFID (2011), ‘A new strategic vision for girls and women: stopping poverty before it starts’, </span><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/67582/strategic-vision-girls-women.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/67582/strategic-vision-girls-women.pdf</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn20"></a><a href="#_ftnref20">[20]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt"> As outlined in ‘Development for all: Towards a disability-inclusive Australian aid programme’ 2009-2014’ - </span><a href="http://www.ausaid.gov.au/Publications/Pages/8131_1629_9578_8310_297.aspx"><sp